The paper presents new integer linear programming models for solving NP-hard optimization problems in the Stable Marriage problem with Ties and Incomplete lists (SMTI) and its many-to-one generalization, the Hospitals/Residents problem with Ties (HRT). These problems are related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), and robotics (cs.RO).
